					<item>
				<guid>http://www.scpwiki.com/forum/t-8517077#post-4062928</guid>
				<title>(no title)</title>
				<link>http://www.scpwiki.com/forum/t-8517077/scp-4248#post-4062928</link>
				<description></description>
				<pubDate>Mon, 19 Nov 2018 17:59:46 +0000</pubDate>
				<wikidot:authorName>Crow-Cat</wikidot:authorName>				<wikidot:authorUserId>3952131</wikidot:authorUserId>				<content:encoded>
					<![CDATA[
						 <p>Even though I've read team bird, I'm&#8230;confused.</p> <div class="collapsible-block"> <div class="collapsible-block-folded"><a class="collapsible-block-link" href="javascript:;">Spoilers</a></div> <div class="collapsible-block-unfolded" style="display:none"> <div class="collapsible-block-unfolded-link"><a class="collapsible-block-link" href="javascript:;">-&nbsp;Close</a></div> <div class="collapsible-block-content"> <p>If this is happening in a universe where the BE-Migration scenario didn't happen, why is documentation for <a href="http://www.scp-wiki.net/scp-3570">EE-3570</a> and <a href="http://www.scp-wiki.net/scp-3632">SCP-3632</a> here? EE-3570 only happened in the BE-scenario, and unless I misread the team bird entries, Thoth shouldn't be able to maintain SCP-3632 because he is/was bleeding out due to either his encounter with Akheilos or Jehovah?</p> </div> </div> </div> 
				 	]]>
				</content:encoded>							</item>
