					<item>
				<guid>http://www.scpwiki.com/forum/t-8517077#post-4055651</guid>
				<title>(no title)</title>
				<link>http://www.scpwiki.com/forum/t-8517077/scp-4248#post-4055651</link>
				<description></description>
				<pubDate>Sun, 11 Nov 2018 04:16:46 +0000</pubDate>
				<wikidot:authorName>Melissanoma</wikidot:authorName>				<wikidot:authorUserId>3260593</wikidot:authorUserId>				<content:encoded>
					<![CDATA[
						 <p>If the year is first, then it almost always means it is going in decreasing order of magnitude. This is often done in computers because it can be treated as a simple number making them easy to sort. e.g. 2018/8/11 becomes 20180811.</p> <p>If the year is last then yeah, that be ambiguous.</p> 
				 	]]>
				</content:encoded>							</item>
					<item>
				<guid>http://www.scpwiki.com/forum/t-8517077#post-4055329</guid>
				<title>SCP-2591?</title>
				<link>http://www.scpwiki.com/forum/t-8517077/scp-4248#post-4055329</link>
				<description></description>
				<pubDate>Sat, 10 Nov 2018 18:19:47 +0000</pubDate>
				<wikidot:authorName>Greenwake</wikidot:authorName>				<wikidot:authorUserId>3157935</wikidot:authorUserId>				<content:encoded>
					<![CDATA[
						 <p>Is this SCP related to <a href="http://www.scp-wiki.net/scp-2591">2591</a>? I noticed that the page for SCP-2591 has this sentence in an interview log:</p> <blockquote> <p><strong>SCP-2591:</strong> My eyes became as painted dragons of justice in the alphabet picture books of hell!</p> </blockquote> <p>The part about &quot;alphabet picture books of hell&quot; sounds a whole lot like this SCP. Is it a coincidence or a implied connection?</p> 
				 	]]>
				</content:encoded>							</item>
